Ban said Wednesday during a conference call that he plans to meet this month with foreign ministers from five permanent countries present on the council - the US, Russia, China, England and France - on the sidelines of the General Assembly's ministerial session to discuss Syria.
Ban expressed regret that divisions in the council and between the Syrian people and regional powers "have made this situation unsolvable."
Ban urged the five permanent members to show the solidarity and unity shown when they managed to strike a deal on Iran's nuclear weapons, thus addressing the crisis in Syria.
