"It is framing even more the right, which is not good for anyone, nor for PSD," Blăjuţ said.
He said he was not interested in a candidacy in the upcoming local elections, denying rumours of his intention to enroll in the race for the City Hall.
I also said that I do not want to run for any local office.
I am still thinking about whether to continue as an MP in the future term.
I tried to appeal to the unit for Iasi and in the discussions on the halls, with the other MPs, and I was accused of wanting to make an image.
I don't want to, but we can't go on like this anymore.
"If people voted for us, it doesn't mean they're stupid to vote for us if they don't see anything," said Blăjuţ, who appreciated that the main reason why the electorate is no longer interested in politics is the hypocrisy of elected officials.
A colleague from Tatarași said that the money is not enough and he has to go by bus.
Let's not be hypocritical.
It's not a little money.
Sometimes I'm ashamed to raise the money from the cashier.
At the end of the mandate I will make a report with everything I have spent, apart from the salaries of the employees in the cabinet and its maintenance.
I happened to pick up in a month and 30,000 lei, with all the transport, accommodation and the rest.
"To say a parliamentarian that the money is not enough is pure hypocrisy," Blăjuţ concluded.
